    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Paolo Giovio (?) (Brussels, 6 October 1532)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">This news has arrived: after the Turks’ retreat the
                            Emperor decided to head to Italy from Linz. When King Ferdinand I heard
                            about this, he hastened to the Emperor with a change of horses to
                            convince him to postpone his trip if he wishes to see him, his wife, and
                            his child in one piece. He finally managed to convince him to go to
                            Vienna and negotiate there what is going to happen to Hungary. They
                            embarked on a boat on 23 September, and they do not know if they
                            followed Roggendorf, who had been sent to Esztergom, or if they went to
                            Vienna. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15321006_1_1.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad eundem.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">According to Fest, he
                        is Paolo Giovio, see <hi rend="smallcap">Fest</hi> 1927, 202.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Nova haec sunt audita his superioribus diebus: imperator noster
                    Turcae retrocessione decreverat, ut omnes omnium, quae, ex curia huc missae
                    sunt, litterae declarabant, ut ex <placeName>Lincio</placeName> ad
                        <placeName>Italiam</placeName> recta contenderet. Vero cum hoc rex
                        <persName>Ferdinandus</persName> certo accepisset, equis cursoriis statim
                    sese commisit, ac itinere et diurno et nocturno ad
                        <persName>caesarem</persName><placeName>Lincio</placeName> venit, cui
                    suadere coepit, ut profectionem Italicam, si eum, <choice>
                        <orig>coniuges</orig>
                        <supplied>coniugem</supplied>
                    </choice>, liberos, denique <placeName>Austriam</placeName> patriam suam salvam
                    esse vellet, hoc tempore praetermitteret. Quem magnis licet difficultatibus et
                    laboribus, eo tamen perduxit, ut consenserit se velle
                        <placeName>Wiennam</placeName> descendere, et istic tractare, quam
                    expeditionem ad <placeName>Hungariam</placeName> aut rex solus aut uterque
                    essent facturi; qui conscendisse autem dicitur in navem
                        <placeName>Lincii</placeName> vigesimatertia Septembris praeteriti. Quid
                    autem nunc agant et ubi sint, <choice>
                        <orig>subsequanturque</orig>
                        <supplied>subsequanturne</supplied>
                    </choice><persName>Wilhelmum a Rogendorff</persName> decimaquarta mensis eiusdem
                    Septembris ex <placeName>Lincio</placeName> cum parte </p>
                <pb facs="15321006_1_2.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">exercitus caesariani ad liberandum ab obsidione
                        <placeName>Strigonium</placeName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.2"
                        >Esztergom.</note> praemissum, an <placeName>Wiennae</placeName> eventum
                    expeditionis eiusdem <persName>Rogendorff</persName><choice>
                        <orig>praesolentur</orig>
                        <supplied>praestolentur</supplied>
                    </choice>, est adhuc incertum. Quicquid audicerimus, faciam te certiorem. Vale. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 6. Octobris 1532. </p>
            </div>
        </body>
